  "commit": "8e5aedc",
  "commitMessage": "test(routing): compute content-length dynamically in middleware specs (#109)\n\nTwo tests in route-registry-middleware.spec.ts hardcode\ncontent-length values that don't match the JSON payload they then\nsend: '13' for {\"number\":5} (12 bytes) and '27' for\n{\"name\":\"John\",\"age\":30} (24 bytes). The tests pass today only\nbecause the implementation relies on uWS's isLast flag rather\nthan validating content-length, but the headers misrepresent the\nHTTP behavior real uWebSockets.js performs.\n\nCompute content-length from Buffer.byteLength(bodyData) at the\ntop of each test, where bodyData is already the JSON string we'll\nlater send via onData. Body and header now agree by construction\nand a future change to either won't drift them apart.\n\nThe third middleware test (around line 312) was already doing this\nvia String(bodyBuffer.length); this change brings the other two in\nline.\n\nCloses #83.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
